Both outputs emitted in the bundle directory and the transcript validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

**Summary of analyses (25 iterations, n=50,000, baseline response 16.9%):**

- **Negative predictors** (independently significant in multivariable model): feature_051 (ordinal 0/1/2; 21.1%→15.7%→11.1%; p=2e-95), feature_013 (binary; p=2e-34), feature_011 (continuous; p=2e-33), feature_067 (binary; p=4e-19), feature_063 (continuous; p=5e-4).
- **Positive predictors**: feature_006 (binary; p=2e-6), feature_092 (continuous, threshold-like; p=2e-3), feature_099, feature_007, feature_039.
- **Strongest interaction**: feature_092 amplifies the binary positive features — feature_006:feature_092 OR=1.81 (p=1.6e-6), feature_007:feature_092 (p=7e-8), feature_039:feature_092 (p=2e-7). The joint upper subgroup (feature_006=1 ∧ feature_092 top quintile, n=2,927) reaches 23.2% response.
- **Refuted**: age (p=0.78), smoking (p≥0.65), histology (p=0.16), feature_064 (p=0.78), and after adjustment race (p=0.13). No racial/insurance disparity in receipt of feature_006 (p=0.67/0.26).
